One such example, Neighbourhood Preserving Embedding (NPE) aims to preserve the local neighbourhood structure of the data once projected onto the manifold17. That is, communities, patterns, or between-group differences that exist among datasets in the high-dimensional setting are maximally preserved within the low-dimensional subspace. Local neighbourhoods are typically defined based on the Euclidean distance between samples in the high-dimensional image space, however it is possible to introduce other constraints in order to conduct NPE in a supervised setting (Fig. 1)17,24. For example, restricting local neighbourhoods to only include subjects from the same class, or diagnostic group, to enhance separation in the low-dimensional space.Figure 1
